Two judges in London rejected a judicial review application. Bamber challenged a refusal by the Criminal Cases Review Commission (CCRC) to refer his case back to the circuit court. After the CCRC asked the government it should stop the appeal and halt the ruling on February 25, 2015, the Conservative Government blocked the appeal. Since then, seven appeals have yet to proceed.

Two cases are still unresolved in the European Court of Humans (ECHA), which hears cases on the rights to medical procedures while in private. Under a law to ban the practice, the ECHA said in July 2012 that "[t]he procedure will not be tolerated in an institution with an obligation to protect patient confidentiality or safety."

